ribution. This extinction curve\nhas relatively steep FUV rise and smaller 2175 Angstroms bump, resembling the\nobserved extinction curve of some regions in the Large Magellanic Cloud.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jun 2003 09:40:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
